# HTML semantics and accessibility

## Interactive controls ‚Äî real buttons only

Do **not** use non-button elements as click targets for actions. This is **forbidden**:

- `<div role="button">` / `<span role="button">`
- Any element with `role="button"` that is not a native **`<button>`** (or an approved styleguide **`Button`** wrapper around one)
- Hand-rolled ‚Äúbuttons‚Äù that rely on `tabIndex={0}` + `onKeyDown` on a `div`/`span` instead of a real button

### Required pattern (in order)

1. **Prefer TailAdmin UI** ‚Äî `Button`, inputs, and related primitives from `src/components/ui/` when they fit (see **`rules-typescript-clean-code.mdc`** ¬ß design system).
2. **Otherwise use native `<button>`** ‚Äî `type="button"` for actions that are not form submit; style via SCSS modules or styleguide variants. Reset browser chrome in CSS when needed (`border: none; background: none;` etc.) ‚Äî do **not** substitute a `div`.

### Anti-pattern

```tsx
// FORBIDDEN
<div
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={onToggle}
  onKeyDown={(event) => {
    if (event.key === "Enter" || event.key === " ") {
      onToggle();
    }
  }}
>
  {title}
</div>
```

### Preferred pattern

```tsx
// Styleguide when available
<Button variant={ButtonVariantEnum.GHOST} onClick={onToggle} text={title} />

// Or native button + module styles
<button type="button" className={styles.AccordionSection_titleButton} onClick={onToggle}>
  {title}
</button>
```

## Other semantics (changed markup)

- **Links vs buttons:** use **`<a href="‚Ä¶">`** for navigation; **`<button type="button">`** (or styleguide **`Button`**) for in-page actions. Do not use `<a href="#">` or `<div onClick>` for actions.
- **Forms:** associate **`label`** with **`input`** via `htmlFor` / `id` for new fields.
- **Headings:** preserve logical heading order in touched templates; do not skip levels for styling.
- **ARIA:** add roles/states only when native semantics are insufficient; do not duplicate what `<button>` already provides.
- **Images:** intentional `alt` text or decorative `alt=""`.

## When reviewing or refactoring

- Flag every new **`role="button"`** on non-`<button>` elements as **`[x]`** ‚Äî merge blocker unless an documented, reviewed exception exists (rare; prefer fixing the markup).
- Existing legacy usages should be migrated to `<button>` or styleguide **`Button`** when the file is already being changed for the ticket.

